## Multi-Agent Orchestration

This project uses the [Agent Orchestrator](https://github.com/zanijr/claudesubagents) framework for coordinating AI agents.

### Quick Start

```bash
# Route a task to the best agent
/orchestrator:route "analyze this code for security issues"

# List available agents
/orchestrator:list

# Check status of running tasks
/orchestrator:status

# View pending escalations
/orchestrator:escalations
```

### Available Agents

The orchestrator will automatically select the best agent based on task requirements:

| Agent | Capabilities | Triggers |
|-------|-------------|----------|
| code-analyzer | code-review, static-analysis | analyze, review, quality |
| task-validator | validation, completion-check | validate, verify, done |
| security-scanner | security, vulnerability-scan | security, audit, scan |

### Project-Specific Agents

Add custom agents in `.claude/agents/project/`:

1. Create a new `.md` file using the template from `.claude/orchestrator/templates/new-agent.md`
2. Define capabilities and triggers in the frontmatter
3. Agent auto-registers on next orchestrator run

### Configuration

See `orchestrator.config.json` for:
- Enabled/disabled agents
- Retry settings (default: 3 retries, then escalate)
- Success threshold (default: 95%)
- Dashboard URL

### Retry & Escalation

Tasks automatically retry up to 3 times on failure:
1. First retry: Same agent, after 1 second
2. Second retry: Same agent, after 2 seconds
3. Third retry: Different agent (if available), after 4 seconds
4. After 3 failures: Escalated to user for decision

### Task Lifecycle

```
Submitted → Dispatching → Running → [Success/Failure]
                              ↓
                         [If Failed]
                              ↓
                    Retrying (up to 3x)
                              ↓
                    [If Still Failing]
                              ↓
                         Escalated
                              ↓
                    [User Decision]
                              ↓
              [Retry / Modify / Cancel]
```

### Validation

The `task-validator` agent automatically validates completions to ensure:
- Work is actually done, not just claimed complete
- Output matches task requirements
- No placeholder or mock data
- 95% confidence threshold met
